Package gov.nist.blockmatrixtimestamped

Class Tensor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nist.blockmatrixtimestamped.Tensor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - any type to be stored
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    public class Tensor<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Tensor auxiliary data structure. This data structure is "square" multidimensional array, where the number of dimensions and width of dimensions can be specified. Once created, the size of the array and dimensions is fixed.

      • get

        public T get​(int... indexes)
      throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Access the element in tensor. You can either use a multidimensional indexing or the underlying one-dimensional index. If dimCount is 4, the multidimensional indexes look like {i1, i2, i3, i4} and one-dimensional index is just {i}, where i = i1*width^3 + i2*width^2 + i3*width + i4. Return null if the given location has not been written to yet.
        Parameters:
        indexes - indexes of the element. Either 1 or dimCount indexes must be present. Each index must be in the interval [0 .. dimCount). If one-dimensional indexing is used, the index must be in the interval [0 .. width^dimCount).
        Returns:
        the element at the given index
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if any index is not in the required interval or the indexes array is not of proper length

      • set

        public T set​(T value,
             int... indexes)
        Set the provided value to the given index. Return the previous value at the given index. Return null if the location has not yet been written to. You can either use a multidimensional indexing or the underlying one-dimensional index. If dimCount is 4, the multidimensional indexes look like {i1, i2, i3, i4} and one-dimensional index is just {i}, where i = i1*width^3 + i2*width^2 + i3*width + i4.
        Parameters:
        value - value to be set
        indexes - indexes of the element. Either 1 or dimCount indexes must be present. Each index must be in the interval [0 .. dimCount). If one-dimensional indexing is used, the index must be in the interval [0 .. width^dimCount).
        Returns:
        the value that was at this index before. Null if the location has not yet been written to.

      • getLine

        public java.util.Collection<T> getLine​(int varDimIdx,
                                       int... fixedIndexes)
                                throws java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException
        Get the line of values in the tensor by letting one index vary and fixing all other indexes. Returns an immutable view of the tensor.
        Parameters:
        varDimIdx - index of the variable index (if 4 dimensions and we want 2nd index to vary, it should be 1). Should be in the interval [0 .. dimCount).
        fixedIndexes - array of other indexes that are fixed, should not include the variable index. For example, if 4 dimensions and we want to access line at {2, 1, x, 5}, where x is a variable index, varDimIdx should be 2 and fixedIndexes should be {2, 1, 5}. Length of the array should be dimCount-1. Each index should be in the interval [0 .. width).
        Returns:
        immutable view of the line
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if any requirement for the arguments is not fulfilled

      • iterator

        public java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()
        Return iterator of the entire tensor. Iterates over the underlying array. The same as iterating using get method with one-dimensional index varying from 0 to width^dimCount-1.
        Specified by:
        iterator in interface java.lang.Iterable<T>
        Returns:
